description.narrative: The objective of the Social Assistance System Modernization Project for Romania is to improve the overall performance of Romania's social assistance system by strengthening performance management, improving equity, improving administrative efficiency and reducing error and fraud. This restructuring have following changes: (i) closing date is extend the project by 23 months, from September 30, 2014, to August 30, 2016; and (ii) change to Disbursement Linked Indicators (DLIs): amend two DLIs which are expected to be fully met in content, but for whose description needs updating to reflect circumstances and reforms not envisaged at the time of project design.
